<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2010-04-01</DATELINE><TITLE>Testing the Donor</TITLE><BODY>The transplantation of tissues from donor to recipient is a fundamental part of medicine today. A range of tissues including bone, skin, tendons, heart valves, corneas etc. are collected from suitable donors and transplanted into those patients for whom tissue transplant would have clinical benefit.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>